FBIS4-42477 "drweu108aa_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-108 Daily Report 3 Jun 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS UN To Cancel Talks If Serb Withdrawal Not Complete UN To Cancel Talks If Serb Withdrawal Not Complete AU0306193794 Paris AFP in English 1928 GMT 3 Jun 94 AU0306193794 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Geneva, June 3 (AFP) -- The United Nations Friday [3 June] warned it would cancel scheduled peace talks on Saturday if Bosnian Serb forces did not fully withdraw from around Gorazde in eastern Bosnia. Talks on a truce should have begun here Thursday, but Bosnian Moslems refused to attend so long as Bosnian Serbs continued to occupy the UN-declared exclusion zone around Gorazde from which they had promised to pull out.
